The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 September is 3,130 (362.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 September, there were 123 new confirmed cases (14.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 August, there were 52 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 137% (71 extra cases).
